    <note>Chang(2) Tong [7001] His Henei jun ancestors included a great minister (zaixiang) of Tang Daizong, Gun [3006]. Tong was buried in Suzhou, Wuxian. He was Chang(2) Gou's [7118] grandson, Anmin's [7000] son, Teng(1) You(1)'s [7350] son-in-law and Fang(1) Zi's [603] 's sister's husband. He was the father-in-law of Su(1) Shide's [1504] son, Pin [3765], and Fang(1) Zi's [603] son, Dao [3302]. His grandson, Liangsun [3007], held a minor fiscal post in 1189, another grandson, Yusun [3010], was Tiju Guangdong shibo in 1213 and again in 1217, and his great grandson, Mao [3008], was promoted from Liangzhe yunpan to yunfu in 1268 and advanced to Hubu shilang in 1269. These descendants had settled in Jiaxing, Haiyan xian. Tong impeached Lin(1) Zhongkan [1159] in 1133. CZ, 191.17b; Fujian TZ, 'zhiguan,' 5.26b; Xianchun Linan zhi, 50.12b; HTZ, 150.2b; Guangdong TZ, 16.5b; SHY:ZG, 72.51a-51b, 74.45b; SS, 376.1a, 5a, 421.12a; ZZTJ, 225.7257; Wang Yingchen, WJ, 20.250; YLDD, 2367.11a. CBD, 3, 2686-7.[Kinship with Liangsun is not yet checked. 與常良孫的親戚關係未考。]</note>
